  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my latest update, Instagram does not offer a feature to see who viewed your videos or Stories specifically. You can see the number of views, but not the individual viewers for video posts. For Stories, however, you can see exactly who viewed them.\n\nTo check who viewed your Instagram Stories:\n1. Open Instagram and go to your profile.\n2. Tap your profile picture or your Story icon to view your Story.\n3. Swipe up on your Story, or tap on the \"Seen by\" text at the bottom left corner.\n\nThis will show you a list of people who have viewed your Story.\n\nFor regular video posts, you can only see the total view count by doing the following:\n1. Open Instagram and go to your profile.\n2. Tap on the video post you\u2019re interested in.\n3. Below the video, you will see the view count, but not the specific viewers.\n\nIf you're interested in more detailed analytics, you might consider switching to an Instagram Business account. Business accounts provide more insights into audience engagement, though they still don't show specific viewers for videos.",
